program: WHILE
##
## Ends in an error in state: 0.
##
## program' -> . program [ # ]
##
## The known suffix of the stack is as follows:
##
##

expected a program

Note: a Liss program has the shape `pre { P } cmd post { Q }`, where `P` and `Q` are formulas and `cmd` is a command.

program: PRE WHILE
##
## Ends in an error in state: 1.
##
## program -> PRE . LBRACE formula RBRACE cmd POST LBRACE formula RBRACE EOF [ # ]
##
## The known suffix of the stack is as follows:
## PRE
##

expected `{` to open the precondition

Note: the precondition is written `pre { formula }`.

program: PRE LBRACE WHILE
##
## Ends in an error in state: 2.
##
## program -> PRE LBRACE . formula RBRACE cmd POST LBRACE formula RBRACE EOF [ # ]
##
## The known suffix of the stack is as follows:
## PRE LBRACE
##

expected a formula

Note: a formula is `true`, `false`, an atom like `x = 0`, `~F`, parentheses, or a connective `/\`, `\/`, `=>`, `<=>`.

program: PRE LBRACE TILDE WHILE
