expected `}` to close the precondition, or a logical connective

Note: the precondition is `pre { F }` — a `}` is needed to close. To extend the formula, use `/\`, `\/`, `=>`, `<=>`.

program: PRE LBRACE FALSE RBRACE WEDGE
##
## Ends in an error in state: 46.
##
## program -> PRE LBRACE formula RBRACE . cmd POST LBRACE formula RBRACE EOF [ # ]
##
## The known suffix of the stack is as follows:
## PRE LBRACE formula RBRACE
##

expected a command

Note: a command is `skip`, `x := e`, `if c then ... else ... end`, `while c invariant { I } do ... end`, `assert { F }`, or `assume { F }`. Commands chain with `;`.

program: PRE LBRACE FALSE RBRACE WHILE WHILE
##
## Ends in an error in state: 47.
